channel.title: Interleaved RSS Feed
channel.description: This is an interleaved feed of the most recent entries from each RSS source, skipping any feeds with errors.

item.title: Police on campus at Columbia and UCLA as protests disrupt colleges nationwide
item.description: Over 300 demonstrators were arrested at Columbia University and City College of New York after police cracked down on people protesting Israel's war in Gaza. Follow for live updates.

item.title: College protests updates: UCLA cancels all classes due to 'violence' overnight
item.description: Protests have broken out at colleges and universities across the country in connection with the war in Gaza.

item.title: Markets await updates from Chair Powell as Fed set to keep interest rates at 23-year high
item.description: The Federal Reserve is expected to announce Wednesday that it will hold its key interest rate steady for the sixth-straight meeting.

item.title: CVS Health chops 2024 forecast as cost struggles with Medicare Advantage persist
item.description: CVS Health missed first-quarter expectations and chopped its 2024 outlook more than a dollar below Wall Street’s forecast

item.title: April 30, 2024 - US university protests
item.description: Over 100 demonstrators were arrested at Columbia University and City College of New York after police cracked down on people protesting Israel's war in Gaza.

item.title: United Methodists repeal their church’s longstanding ban on LGBTQ clergy
item.description: United Methodists, at major conference, repeal their church’s longstanding ban on LGBTQ clergy

item.title: Ex-attorney for Daniels and McDougal testifies in Trump trial
item.description: Attorney Keith Davidson, a key witness who represented Stormy Daniels and Karen McDougal, was questioned Tuesday by prosecutors about the negotiations that led to Daniels' tabloid deal and hush money payment during the Donald Trump criminal trial.

item.title: WATCH: Meet Bella, the 5-legged puppy up for adoption
item.description: Bella has a very rare condition known as dimelia.

item.title: April 29, 2024 - Columbia begins suspending student protesters
item.description: The deadline set by Columbia University for demonstrators to vacate an encampment there or face suspension has passed.

item.title: Apple juice recalled due to high arsenic levels, sold at Whole Foods, Kroger and more
item.description: Apple juice from Martinelli's sold at five major grocery retailers has been recalled due to high levels of arsenic.
